<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,284,385]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis box="[264,438,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: gonocoxa elongated; distiphallus long, surpassing apex of posterior process of gonocoxa by a distance equivalent to its length; lateral aedeagal apodeme not surpassing gonocoxal margins; gonostylus hook shaped (
<figureCitation box="[896,967,359,385]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 ­ 6" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1540,1564]" captionTargetBox="[425,1157,444,1521]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[425,1158,444,1521]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4 ­ 6. – Fig. 4: Spermathecae of Crocidium dasypolium Hesse, 1963; Figs. 5 ­ 6 – Crocidium dichopticum Hesse, 1963: 5. Male genitalia; 6. Spermathecae" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155825/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[950,967,359,385]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155825/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" targetBox="[425,1157,444,1521]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,1540,1598]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,432,1540,1564]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">FIGURES 4­6.</emphasis>
– Fig. 4: Spermathecae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1963" authorityName="Hesse" authorityYear="1963" box="[723,1106,1540,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Crocidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dasypolium">
<emphasis box="[723,966,1541,1564]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Crocidium dasypolium</emphasis>
Hesse, 1963
</taxonomicName>
; Figs. 5­6 – 
<taxonomicName authority="Hesse, 1963: 5" authorityName="Hesse" authorityPageNumber="5" authorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Crocidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dichopticum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Crocidium dichopticum</emphasis>
Hesse, 1963: 5
</taxonomicName>
. Male genitalia; 6. Spermathecae
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1324,1650,1876]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis box="[312,478,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Spermathecae</emphasis>
: spermathecae elliptical with longitudinal axis equivalent to 
<number box="[1247,1258,1650,1676]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1270,1285,1650,1676]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="3.0">3</number>
of sperm pump length; spermathecal ducts very long, 
<number box="[898,927,1690,1716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="21.0">21</number>
times longer than sperm pump, enlarged on apical portion and forming a membranous cup in the attachment to the reservoir, uniting to form a short common spermathecal duct; sperm pump placed at nearly basal 
<number box="[333,343,1810,1836]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[355,386,1810,1836]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="18.0">18</number>
of the spermathecal duct; sclerotized collars developed on both ends of sperm pumps. (
<figureCitation box="[366,437,1850,1876]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 ­ 6" captionStartId="4.[264,383,1540,1564]" captionTargetBox="[425,1157,444,1521]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[425,1158,444,1521]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4 ­ 6. – Fig. 4: Spermathecae of Crocidium dasypolium Hesse, 1963; Figs. 5 ­ 6 – Crocidium dichopticum Hesse, 1963: 5. Male genitalia; 6. Spermathecae" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/155825/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[420,437,1850,1876]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
